# UI / UX Standards

## Tech Stack (Official Frontend)

- **Vite 7 + React 19 + TypeScript** — `sercop-unified/frontend/`
- **Chakra UI 3 + Emotion** for all UI components
- **react-router-dom 7** for navigation
- **i18next** for internationalization (all user-visible strings must be translatable)
- **Framer Motion** for animations (use sparingly)
- **Recharts** for data visualization

## Component Structure

```
src/
  components/           → Reusable, stateless/presentational
  pages/                → Route-level components (thin, delegate to components)
    cp/                 → Compras Públicas / AI features
    client/             → Client portal pages
  services/             → API calls via apiClient.ts (no fetch() directly in components)
  realtime/             → WebSocket / SignalR providers
  theme.ts              → Chakra theme overrides (single source of truth for colors/fonts)
  styles/               → Global CSS (minimal — prefer Chakra props)
```

## Component Rules

```tsx
// ✅ Functional components with explicit TypeScript props
interface TenderCardProps {
  tenderId: string;
  title: string;
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
}

export const TenderCard: React.FC<TenderCardProps> = ({ tenderId, title, onSelect }) => {
  return (
    <Box p={4} borderRadius="md" onClick={() => onSelect(tenderId)}>
      <Text fontWeight="bold">{title}</Text>
    </Box>
  );
};

// ❌ Never use default exports for components (use named exports)
// ❌ Never call fetch() directly in a component — use services/
```

## State Management

- **Local state**: `useState`, `useReducer` for component-level
- **Shared state**: React Context (`AuthContext`, `BrandContext`) for global concerns
- **Server state**: custom hooks wrapping service calls with loading/error states
- No Redux — keep it simple

## API Calls Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ All API calls via services/
import { gptsercopService } from '../services/gptsercopService';

const { data, isLoading, error } = useTenderSearch(query);

// ✅ Service pattern
export const gptsercopService = {
  analyze: async (tenderId: string) =>
    apiClient.post(`/api/v1/sercop/core-flow/analyze`, { tenderId }),
};
```

## Accessibility (a11y)

- All interactive elements need `aria-label` or visible text
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 (WCAG AA)
- Keyboard navigation must work for all flows
- Use `@axe-core/playwright` in E2E to catch a11y regressions
- Never disable focus outlines

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: use Chakra responsive array syntax `fontSize={['sm', 'md', 'lg']}`
- Test on 375px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop)
- `styles/mobile.css` for mobile-specific overrides when Chakra props are insufficient

## Realtime (SignalR / WebSocket)

- Realtime connections managed in `realtime/` providers — never in page components
- Clean up subscriptions on unmount with `useEffect` cleanup function
- Graceful degradation: app must work if realtime is unavailable

## Do / Don't

- ✅ Use Chakra theme tokens — never hardcode hex colors in components
- ✅ i18n every user-facing string via `useTranslation()`
- ✅ Lazy-load heavy pages with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`
- ❌ Never import from `apps/*-portal` — those are deprecated
- ❌ Never bypass `AuthContext` for protected views
- ❌ Never use inline styles (use Chakra props or theme)
